m Aratu and continued until arrival 3rd load terminal. We ended up lifting 44,012 MT, just over the CP min of 44k by minimizing bunker stem at NOLA and commingling a small parcel of membrane grade CSS. First load berth in Miss River required a hold in tug for 2 days, this $66k was rebilled. Only real issue operationally was the expired SSEC which vessel renewed whilst laden, under the radar and in the middle of the night at Chaguaramas. Free pratique was subsequently granted prior arrival Itaqui ensuring our initial NOR was valid and the 7 days waiting for berth counted as laytime. The 2 port load and 6 port discharge took 77 days which is 17 longer than generated. 13 of these were invoiced as demurrage at $31k pdpr while the remainder is accounted for in river transit times and an additional load terminal at Plaquemine. Port costs down $115k mainly due cancellation of Punta Pereira and overstatement of Plaquemine costs by $60k (hold in tugs initially assumed for our account in Miss River)."},{"modifiedDate":"2023-03-30T12:46:04.913","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"day extended at Santos - dem estimate updated"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-03-08T17:50:15.603","modifiedByFull":"Ervasti, Josh","remark":"freight corrected for 1 port uruguay"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-03-08T16:00:05.947","modifiedByFull":"Ervasti, Josh","remark":"arrival Itaqui entered - waiting 7 days for berthing updated dems @ 31kpdy"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-03-08T15:59:45.69","modifiedByFull":"Ervasti, Josh","remark":"Punta perreira removed as disport - canceled"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-03-02T17:42:08.77","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"bunker invoice approved 58k less than expected"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-02-17T20:42:38.247","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"updated financials basis PDAs"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-01-27T14:47:15.65","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"bunker stem updated in Miss River / expect to complete voyage with single stem"},{"modifiedD